column5: Went to the cottage to check things out.  Crossing the bridge at the narrows -wide open water as far as I could see westward and for 500 yds to the east.
if you mean gannon narrows i have a cottage just up the road and it was open tuesday.  first year at the cottage and am a little worried with the lake levels so low

Don't be concerned, that water is open all winter long no matter how cold.  And don't worry about the water levels, there will be plenty of water come early May. Check out this site for some perspective on the seasonal fluctuations.
You might want to go tomorrow with 100km plus winds forcasted, esp if theirs any trees close by.
Good point.  Lots of trees.  Better check out tomorrow.
